data.name: Sample - MISP - 2.2.0
data.description: Sample playbooks for "MISP" connector. If you are planning to use any of the sample playbooks in your environment, ensure that you clone those playbooks and move them to a different collection, since the sample playbook collection gets deleted during connector upgrade and delete.

workflows.name: Get Users
workflows.description: Retrieves a list of all available users from MISP

workflows.name: Add Tag
workflows.description: Adds a tag in MISP based on the parameters that you have specified.

workflows.description: Search for events or attributes in MISP

workflows.name: Get Organizations
workflows.description: Retrieves a list of all available Organizations from MISP

workflows.name: Delete Event
workflows.description: Delete event from MISP using event ID

workflows.name: Add Tag to Event
workflows.description: Adds an specific tag to specific event which was already created in MISP based on the event ID that you specify

workflows.name: Get Event
workflows.description: Get event information using event ID

workflows.name: Get Events List
workflows.description: Retrieves information about events from MISP

workflows.name: File Hash / Domain / IP / URL > MISP > Enrichment
workflows.description: Retrieve the reputation of indicator of type ‘File Hash / Domain / IP / URL’ using Fortinet FortiGuard Threat Intelligence.
